&nbsp;Brave fire fighters from Newcastle battled a blazing fire, that erupted at the Glencoe Correctional Services building yesterday morning. The blaze completely gutted the building and one hundred prisoners from the facility, had to be evacuated to safety to a nearby ground.SAPS from Northern Natal had to be called in to assist the warders in safeguarding the prisoners. An investigation was initiated by the Department of Correctional Services into the cause of the blaze.SAPS spokesperson, Colonel Jay Naicker said that the cause of the fire was unknown at this stage. All the prisoners were taken to various correctional services facilities within the area and no one was injured during the blaze, concluded Naicker.